SIMPLE: gimmal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gimmal
<hw>Gim"mal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. the same word
as <ets>gemel</ets>. See <er>Gemel</er>, and cf. <er>Gimbal</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Joined work whose parts move within each other; a pair
or series of interlocked rings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A quaint piece of machinery; a gimmer.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gimmal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gimmal
<hw>Gim"mal</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Made or consisting of interlocked
rings or links; <as>as, <ex>gimmal</ex> mail</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In their pale dull mouths the <qex>gimmal</qex> bit⟦br⟧
Lies foul with chewed grass.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gimmal joint</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Gimbal
joint</cref>, under <er>Gimbal</er>.</cd></cs></p>

<p><ent>Gimmor</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Gimmer</ent>⟦br⟧
